  "prompt": "Can a person who is blind from birth dream?",
  "response": "Yes, a person who is blind from birth can dream. However, their dreams may differ from those of sighted individuals. While people who are blind from birth do not experience visual images in their dreams, their dreams are often rich in other sensory experiences such as sounds, touch, taste, and smell. These sensory inputs are representative of how their brains interpret and understand the world around them. Additionally, their dreams can include emotions, narratives, and abstract thoughts, similar to the dream content of sighted people.",
